    {
      "id": "7Lk8lCvfWaMQcSg4o7o8H",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 569.3061412986088,
      "y": 12737.880138357155,
      "width": 3471.875,
      "height": 859.4105136640079,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "hachure",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b2g",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1177224486,
      "version": 1392,
      "versionNonce": 1029085981,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1771307885705,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "- Read-heavy workload -> 100 million DAU each of whihc making 20 req/sec -> 2000 million daiily\n- Expensive queries -> LIke in new feeds computing a user's personalized news feed is going to \n    require joining a bunch of Posts, Followers,Likes all of these across multiple tables thats going\n    to be very expensive to compute so what we can do, we can just cache news feed store with the \n    TTL d of 60 sec and then serve it really quickly from something like redis.\n- High database CPU -> in real life if our database is starting to peg out on its\nCPU , then it would make sense to add a cache in front of it\n- Latency requirements -> In Non functional requirements may be we specified we needed \na 100 millisecond response time on some API, then we could argue or just justify that \nthe database query is going to take too long,especially if it has expensive query, and \nso we will have to cache it.",
      "fontSize": 62.50258281192785,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "- Read-heavy workload -> 100 million DAU each of whihc making 20 req/sec -> 2000 million daiily\n- Expensive queries -> LIke in new feeds computing a user's personalized news feed is going to \n    require joining a bunch of Posts, Followers,Likes all of these across multiple tables thats going\n    to be very expensive to compute so what we can do, we can just cache news feed store with the \n    TTL d of 60 sec and then serve it really quickly from something like redis.\n- High database CPU -> in real life if our database is starting to peg out on its\nCPU , then it would make sense to add a cache in front of it\n- Latency requirements -> In Non functional requirements may be we specified we needed \na 100 millisecond response time on some API, then we could argue or just justify that \nthe database query is going to take too long,especially if it has expensive query, and \nso we will have to cache it.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "jaNkv834bJapCVgZ-Cfqf",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 455.846174254154,
      "y": 13886.611385428532,
      "width": 3300,
      "height": 312.5129140596393,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "hachure",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b2h",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 2079626682,
      "version": 991,
      "versionNonce": 1565126963,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1771307885705,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "How to Introduce Caching -> focus on data that is causing issue that needs to be read frequently\nmay be doesn't change often, or its expensive to fetch or compute these things we can\nfocus on caching. think about cache keys due to interviewer can ask what you are caching\nwhat is the value in our cache? ",
      "fontSize": 62.50258281192786,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "How to Introduce Caching -> focus on data that is causing issue that needs to be read frequently\nmay be doesn't change often, or its expensive to fetch or compute these things we can\nfocus on caching. think about cache keys due to interviewer can ask what you are caching\nwhat is the value in our cache? ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "NdmmIzaFCRjvZ6WnVTc69",
