but it can also cache public, read-heavy API responses with short TTLs.\nFor correctness-critical data like bookings and payments, requests always go to the origin.\nCDN acts as the outermost caching layer, reducing global latency, while application caches and databases handle fresher data.”\n\n7️⃣ One-line rule to remember 🧠\n\nIf wrong data is acceptable → CDN cache it\nIf wrong data breaks business → always hit origin\n\n",
